This code snippet is for a video I did on how to add a Tooltip on your Webflow website. Video can be found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PJPnftjUftQ

Header Code:

<!--Tooltip Styling-->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/tippy.js@4/themes/light-border.css"/>

Body Code: 

<!--Tooltip Scripts & Settings-->
<script src="https://unpkg.com/popper.js@1"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/tippy.js@4"></script>
<script>
tippy('.tooltip', {        
 animation: 'fade',    
 duration: 200,      
 arrow: true,          
 delay: [0, 50],      
 arrowType: 'sharp',  
 theme: 'light-border',        
 maxWidth: 220,    
 interactive: true,
})
</script>
